commits.commitMessage:
[DSP_PHY] SW implementation of EDGE coprocessors - Viterbi

Description:
    - Added EDGE Viterbi model from the simulator
    - Interfaced it with EGPRS MCS-1 to MCS-4 DSP code
    - EDGE block decoding task is no longer triggered by an interrupt
      (legacy SW interrupt mapped onto INT2, now removed). It is called
      by the idle task conditionally to the flag Launch_EdgeBlockDecodingTask
      which is by LaunchIT2()
    - ViterbiCoproServicing() function is no longer triggered by an
      interrupt (legacy Viterbi interrupt mapped onto INT0, now removed).
      It is called directly in the DSP SW after the EDGE Data block
      decoding is done (i.e., after EDGE_DataDecodeIRPart2())
    - Made idle task interruptible (dsp_main.c)
    - Implemented EDGE coprocessor RAM memory banks (_EDGE_COPRO_RAM0/1)
      as 3 SW buffers: EDGE_COPRO_VITERBI_Soft_Bits_Buffer[], EDGE_COPRO-
      _VITERBI_Decoded_Bits_Buffer[], EDGE_COPRO_VITERBI_Decision_Word-
      _Buffer[]
    - Embraced new code with __SW_EDGE_COPRO__ compilation flag. Compiling
      without this flag is still possible (may be useful as a fallback
      in simulation only)
    - Renamed compilation flag __EDGE_ALTAIR_PHYSDK_ADAPT_TEMP__ into
      __EDGE_CODE__ (to embrace EDGE code in common files)
    - Changed the EC-GSM HWL/DSP interface flag name for block decoding
      request from RX_EC_EARLY_BLOCK_DEC_ENABLE to RX_EC_BLOCK_DEC_REQ
      (what5_h.h, smitfbf.h)

Resolves: ALT1250-1334
Change-Id: I4c61d0e1b6bcd3be1bfa7e0973075a655b650845
